"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-megan-havers-womens-archery-team-gb-south-korea-paris-2024-b2585841.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Havers and GB teammates Bryony Pitman & Penny Healey are seeded 11th following the Women's Archery individual rankings round in Paris  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 456, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 227, \"end\": 229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999672957246866, \"rank\": 2.161038705871341e-05, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 307, \"end\": 314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Target_archery\", \"score\": 0.999533846061966, \"rank\": 0.0004663713389325716, \"text\": \"Archery\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Target_archery\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Target_archery\"}, {\"begin\": 344, \"end\": 349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999962256, \"rank\": 3.756495851862001e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  In the shadow of Napoleon's tomb, a 16-year-old from Leicester became the firstTeam GBathlete to compete atParis 2024.\", \"from\": 457, \"to\": 599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 498, \"end\": 506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9737241221403113e-25, \"text\": \"Napoleon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\"}, {\"begin\": 534, \"end\": 543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leicester_City_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.7215636561100636, \"rank\": 0.3186777859426413, \"text\": \"Leicester\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leicester_City_F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leicester_City_F.C.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Megan Havers, who attended her school prom just a few weeks ago, fired the first shot in anger in the women's archery ranking round.\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 601, \"end\": 606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Koehler\", \"score\": 0.9983908755434119, \"rank\": 0.0008883622473674102, \"text\": \"Megan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Koehler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Megan_Koehler\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I like to shoot first, so I do not get in my own head, that's my rule,\\\" said Havers.\", \"from\": 735, \"to\": 820, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a cool thing to be the first athlete to compete, but I did not do it deliberately!\\\"\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 910, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is fitting that a teenager got Team GB underway, given there are 14 of them in the squad and that these Games signal the passing of the baton from the London 2012 generation.\", \"from\": 912, \"to\": 1089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 946, \"end\": 953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999981451695852, \"rank\": 1.369157397441718e-06, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1066, \"end\": 1077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.285075742933907e-13, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wearing a colourful bracelet made by her school friend Eva, the bucket hat-wearing Havers barely broke sweat on a toasty day in Paris.\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1225, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1219, \"end\": 1224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999962256, \"rank\": 3.756495851862001e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My English GCSE was harder than that,\\\" joked Havers, who has not even picked up her results yet.\", \"from\": 1227, \"to\": 1324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1231, \"end\": 1238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language\", \"score\": 0.9954341200914277, \"rank\": 0.004578454135701288, \"text\": \"English\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/English_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That definitely took more out of me.\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1362, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I came onto this field today and I did not feel the nerves.\", \"from\": 1364, \"to\": 1424, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can officially say I am an Olympian now, which is really cool to say.\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1496, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1454, \"end\": 1462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999996082752517, \"rank\": 3.917249310750159e-07, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have got a lot moreOlympicsin me, I hope.\\\"\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1541, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The archery ranking round is a curiosity of the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 1543, \"to\": 1605, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The traditional pre-Opening Ceremony curtain-raiser is neither televised nor ticketed and involves all 128 archers shooting 72 arrows each on the same field, with total scores producing seedings for individual and team competition.\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1838, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hundreds of journalists gaggled behind the range, peering vaguely at a target more than 100 metres away and doing so for three hours, with no in-venue live scoring offering updates.\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 2021, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is fair to say there will be better spectacles in the next fortnight.\", \"from\": 2022, \"to\": 2094, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A cheer did go up when the first world record of the Games fell at the hands of Korean Lim Sihyeon, who shot 694 to surpass compatriot Kang Chae Young's previous mark of 692 set in 2019.\", \"from\": 2096, \"to\": 2282, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2176, \"end\": 2182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.9992259279201307, \"rank\": 0.0007746458818624781, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2187, \"end\": 2194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Si-hyeon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sihyeon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Si-hyeon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Si-hyeon\"}, {\"begin\": 2231, \"end\": 2235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kang_the_Conqueror\", \"score\": 0.9852587117799669, \"rank\": 0.014961842097149965, \"text\": \"Kang\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kang_the_Conqueror\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kang_the_Conqueror\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Powerhouse Korea have won all nine Olympic titles in the women's team since the sport's inclusion at Seoul 1988.\", \"from\": 2284, \"to\": 2396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2295, \"end\": 2300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9989008628348971, \"rank\": 0.0009762981473689143, \"text\": \"Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 2385, \"end\": 2395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9991516409689681, \"rank\": 0.000848039072285506, \"text\": \"Seoul 1988\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The country's Olympic trials are infamously brutal.\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2449, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you do not turn up on the day, you do not make it and An San missed out on Paris altogether despite becoming the first archer to win three Olympic golds at one Games at Tokyo 2020.\", \"from\": 2450, \"to\": 2633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2528, \"end\": 2533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999962256, \"rank\": 3.756495851862001e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2622, \"end\": 2627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9410889124559803, \"rank\": 0.06259885241578646, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The trials produced a team of Lim, last year's breakout star, and rookies Jeon Hunyoung and Nam Suhyeon, who have only one World Championship cap between them.\", \"from\": 2635, \"to\": 2794, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even so, Nam finished second behind Lim and Jeon placed 13th to earn them top seeding for Sunday's women's team event where they will bid for a tenth successive victory.\", \"from\": 2796, \"to\": 2965, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Korea's success is thanks to world-leading facilities and a professional infrastructure that is the envy of the world - including Team GB's Bryony Pitman.\", \"from\": 2967, \"to\": 3121, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2967, \"end\": 2972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9989008628348971, \"rank\": 0.0009762981473689143, \"text\": \"Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 3097, \"end\": 3104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999981451695852, \"rank\": 1.369157397441718e-06, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 3107, \"end\": 3120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryony_Pitman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bryony Pitman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryony_Pitman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryony_Pitman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not think anyone would really expect anything less (than a world record),\\\" said Pitman.\", \"from\": 3123, \"to\": 3216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3209, \"end\": 3215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pitman_shorthand\", \"score\": 0.9106937842400993, \"rank\": 0.09806393285075887, \"text\": \"Pitman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pitman_shorthand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pitman_shorthand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The money that they put into it is just unlike any other country.\", \"from\": 3218, \"to\": 3284, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They have professional teams.\", \"from\": 3285, \"to\": 3314, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think the last few months, they have had a replica Paris stage set up and they have been shooting against a robot that just puts them in the tens all the time.\", \"from\": 3315, \"to\": 3476, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3368, \"end\": 3373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999962256, \"rank\": 3.756495851862001e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They are as prepared as you could possibly be for an Olympic Games.\\\"\", \"from\": 3478, \"to\": 3547, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tokyo Olympian Pitman finished 41st, Havers 49th and Penny Healey 52nd with Team GB seeded 11th out of 12 teams for the women's team.\", \"from\": 3549, \"to\": 3682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3549, \"end\": 3563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tokyo Olympian\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3549, \"end\": 3563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tokyo Olympian\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3564, \"end\": 3570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pitman_shorthand\", \"score\": 0.9106937842400993, \"rank\": 0.09806393285075887, \"text\": \"Pitman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pitman_shorthand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pitman_shorthand\"}, {\"begin\": 3602, \"end\": 3607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penny\", \"score\": 0.9999998413523042, \"rank\": 1.2827244516877745e-07, \"text\": \"Penny\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penny\"}, {\"begin\": 3608, \"end\": 3614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Healey_Motor_Company\", \"score\": 0.9992142094546446, \"rank\": 0.0007864084801727548, \"text\": \"Healey\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Healey_Motor_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Healey_Motor_Company\"}, {\"begin\": 3625, \"end\": 3632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999981451695852, \"rank\": 1.369157397441718e-06, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With more than \\u00a330M a week raised for Good Causes, including vital funding into elite and grassroots sport, National Lottery players support our Olympic and Paralympic athletes to live their dreams and make the nation proud, as well as providing more opportunities for people to take part in sport.\", \"from\": 3684, \"to\": 3982, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3792, \"end\": 3808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\", \"score\": 0.998797149768408, \"rank\": 0.001204298817869547, \"text\": \"National Lottery\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To find out more visit:www.lotterygoodcauses.org.uk  Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3983, \"to\": 4266, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4087, \"end\": 4098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8051898477589373e-17, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"